ENTRY            A0589   20260204   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0589001   20260204   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 12         37
TITLE      Absence of fusion suppression due to breakup in the
           12C + 7Li reaction
AUTHOR     (A.Mukherjee, M.Dasgupta, D.J.Hinde, H.Timmers,
           R.D.Butt, P.R.S.Gomes)
INSTITUTE  (3AULCBR,3BZLUFF)
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,526,295,2002)
REL-REF    (I,,H.Timmers+,J,NIM/B,136-138,611,1998)
           (I,,H.Timmers+,J,NIM/B,161-163,19,2000)
           (I,,H.Timmers+,J,NIM/A,447,536,2000)
           Details of detector.
SAMPLE     (3-LI-7,ENR=0.999) An existing target of 7-Li/F,
           having 99.9% enrichment of 7Li, was used. The target
           was of thickness ~80 ug/cm2, evaporated onto a
           ~35 ug/cm2 carbon backing. A very thin layer of
           Au (~4 ug/cm2) was deposited on the target for beam
           dose and solid angle normalization. The composition of
           the target was determined by elastic recoil detection
           analysis using a 58Ni beam of energy 60 MeV, which is
           less than half the Coulomb barrier energy for all
           target components. In terms of number of nuclei/cm2,
           the abundance of the various target components
           relative to 7-Li were measured to be: Li:F:C:O:Au =
           1.00 : 1.00+/-0.01 : 0.96+/-0.01 : 0.0427+/-0.0004 :
           0.0069+/-0.0003.
MONITOR    (79-AU-197(6-C-12,EL)79-AU-197,,DA)
DETECTOR   (IOCH) Special ionization chamber. The full energy of
           the ions entering the detector was measured using a
           21 cm long grid electrode, whilst the energy loss
           signal was obtained from a separate 3.2 cm long anode.
FACILITY   (VDGT,3AULCBR) The experiment was performed with a
           12C beam of energy 10.5 MeV, from the 14UD Pelletron
           accelerator.
METHOD     (EDE,SITA,EXTB)
ADD-RES    (ANGD) Angular distributions for nitrogen and F+O+N
HISTORY    (20030709C)
           (20031229U) Last checking has been done.
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              37
COMMON               1          3
EN-CM
MEV
        3.7
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           44
SUBENT        A0589002   20260204   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                  7         30
REACTION   (3-LI-7(6-C-12,FUS),,SIG)
MISC-COL   (MISC) Fusion cross section after correction on low
           energy evaporated residues. See COMMENT
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
           (MISC-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
COMMENT    - By authors. It needs to be emphasized here that
           this cross-section, excluding evaporated residues
           having kinetic energies below 4 MeV and also
           excluding the evaporated residues C and B, is indeed
           the lower limit to the fusion cross-section at this
           energy. To compare with gamma-ray measurements, an
           estimate is needed of the cross- sections of
           evaporated residues with kinetic energies below 4 MeV,
           not available from the present measurement.
           Statistical model calculations performed using the
           code PACE, which reproduces the energy and angular
           dependence of the evaporated residues, predicted the
           contribution of evaporated residues below 4 MeV to be
           20% of the total fusion cross-section. However, to
           take into account the possible dependence of the
           calculation on the various parameters in the code,
           this contribution below 4 MeV has been taken to be
            (20+/-8) %, where the uncertainty has been estimated
           very conservatively.
REL-REF    (A,O0946001,A.Mukherjee+,J,NP/A,596,299,1996)
           (D,,J.Takahashi+,J,PRL,78,30,1997)
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.Mukherjee+,J,PL/B,526,295,2002) From the text
            on p. 299
HISTORY    (20260204U) SD: BIB updated. STATUS added.
           ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
